<type>(<scope>): <description>

# Body is optional — omit it for straightforward changes where the
# subject line is self-explanatory. Only add a body when the *why*
# is non-obvious: a constraint, a tradeoff, or context that isn't
# visible in the diff. Never summarise what the diff already shows.
# Wrap at 72 characters. ============================================|

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]

# ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat      introduce a new feature
# fix       patch a bug
# refactor  code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# docs      documentation only
# test      add or update tests
# chore     maintenance, deps, tooling
# build     build system or external dependencies
# ci        CI configuration files and scripts
# style     formatting, missing semi colons, whitespace
# perf      performance improvement
#
# ── Rules ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Separate subject from body with a blank line
# 2. Subject line ≤ 50 characters total
# 3. Description is lowercase — proper nouns excepted
# 4. Do not end the subject line with a period
# 5. Use the imperative mood: "add feature" not "added feature"
# 6. Wrap the body at 72 characters
# 7. Body explains *why*, never *what* — the diff shows what changed
#
# If applied, this commit will: <description>
#
# ── Scopes ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Scope is the top-level package or directory:
#   palette
# Add a sub-scope only when it provides useful context:
#   palette/delegate
#
# ── Breaking changes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Append ! after type/scope, and/or add a footer:
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
